"Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince," number six in the series by British author J.K.
Rowling will go on sale in July 2005.
The publication date will be simultaneous in several countries.
Bloomsbury Publishing's stock surged with the news.
More than 5 million pre-orders have been received by booksellers worldwide.
10.8 million copies of the first printing and 635,000 audio book copies will be available in July.
Four separate editions are planned for US and UK audiences.
In two separate cases, theft and accidental pre-release sales, injunctions forbidding the leaking of details prior to publication were issued.
